 \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 272, \"end\": 280, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.569143849784561e-20, \"text\": \"Leonardo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 281, \"end\": 288, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0577256240038724e-25, \"text\": \"DaVinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 369, \"end\": 374, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3436503900726333e-13, \"text\": \"Jesus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"nearly everyone\", \"from\": 117, \"to\": 132}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 150, \"to\": 170}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Olympics\", \"from\": 174, \"to\": 192}, {\"ngram\": \"an obscene tableau\", \"from\": 202, \"to\": 220}, {\"ngram\": \"a paganized rendering\", \"from\": 247, \"to\": 268}, {\"ngram\": \"hyper-sexualized transgender performers\", \"from\": 319, \"to\": 358}, {\"ngram\": \"the apostles\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 391}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As if to leave no doubt about their perversity, the scene evenincluded a child.\", \"from\": 393, \"to\": 472, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no doubt\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 416}, {\"ngram\": \"their perversity\", \"from\": 423, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"the scene\", \"from\": 441, \"to\": 450}, {\"ngram\": \"a child\", \"from\": 464, \"to\": 471}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Amid an international public outcry from Christians, the organizers tried to remove all video footage of the segment online, and a spokesman for the International Olympic Committeeissued a weak non-apologyover the weekend, saying \\\"there was never any intention to show disrespect towards any religious group or belief,\\\" that \\\"their intention with the Opening Ceremony was always to celebrate community and tolerance,\\\" and that \\\"if anyone was offended by certain scenes, this was completely unintentional and they were sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 474, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 515, \"end\": 525, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 825, \"end\": 841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opening_ceremony\", \"score\": 0.9434987276975909, \"rank\": 0.05988481197714756, \"text\": \"Opening Ceremony\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opening_ceremony\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Opening_ceremony\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an international public outcry\", \"from\": 479, \"to\": 509}, {\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 541}, {\"ngram\": \"all video footage\", \"from\": 558, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"the segment\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 590}, {\"ngram\": \"a spokesman\", \"from\": 603, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"the International Olympic\", \"from\": 619, \"to\": 644}, {\"ngram\": \"any intention\", \"from\": 721, \"to\": 734}, {\"ngram\": \"any religious group\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"belief\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 791}, {\"ngram\": \"their intention\", \"from\": 800, \"to\": 815}, {\"ngram\": \"community\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 875}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 880, \"to\": 889}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 905, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"certain scenes\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 942}]}, {\"sentence\": \"No intention to offend?\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1024, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"No intention\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1013}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The segment was titled \\\"La C\\u00e8ne sur la scene sur la seine\\\" (The Last Supper on the stage on the Seine).\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1121, \"end\": 1126, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999990454853, \"rank\": 9.54497781733588e-10, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The segment\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1036}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"La C\\u00e8ne sur la scene sur la seine\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1082}, {\"ngram\": \"(The Last Supper\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1100}, {\"ngram\": \"the stage\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1113}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So it was obviously meant to be a sexualized mockery of the Last Supper, as anyone who witnessed the spectacle could easily see.\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1257, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a sexualized mockery\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1181}, {\"ngram\": \"the Last Supper\", \"from\": 1185, \"to\": 1200}, {\"ngram\": \"anyone\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1211}, {\"ngram\": \"the spectacle\", \"from\": 1226, \"to\": 1239}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Bishop Robert Barronsaid in responseto the statement, \\\"Christians were offended because it was offensive, and it was intended to be offensive.\\\"\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1404, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1261, \"end\": 1267, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"score\": 0.9999999898659553, \"rank\": 1.0133988497070258e-08, \"text\": \"Bishop\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bishop\"}, {\"begin\": 1316, \"end\": 1326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"responseto\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"the statement\", \"from\": 1300, \"to\": 1313}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Quite right.\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1417, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even if you did not see the thing, the drag queens who participated were quite open about what they believed they were doing.\", \"from\": 1419, \"to\": 1544, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the thing\", \"from\": 1443, \"to\": 1452}, {\"ngram\": \"the drag queens\", \"from\": 1454, \"to\": 1469}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Barbara Butch, the French LGBT activist who played the role of whatshe called \\\"Olympic Jesus\\\"in the revolting scene, also called it the \\\"New Gay Testament\\\"on her Instagram page.\", \"from\": 1545, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"score\": 0.9999897744159937, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barbara Butch\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barbara_Butch\"}, {\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.5999310862647015, \"rank\": 0.6526916065924061, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}, {\"begin\": 1571, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"score\": 0.9999964514540103, \"rank\": 2.7762827178279314e-06, \"text\": \"LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LGBT\"}, {\"begin\": 17