41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999980389917383, \"rank\": 1.961012022253466e-06, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the outrage\", \"from\": 2234, \"to\": 2245}, {\"ngram\": \"the excuse\", \"from\": 2247, \"to\": 2257}, {\"ngram\": \"their efforts\", \"from\": 2283, \"to\": 2296}, {\"ngram\": \"pervert\", \"from\": 2310, \"to\": 2317}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What's more, the attacks on Christianity were not limited to this one scene.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2426, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2390, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the attacks\", \"from\": 2363, \"to\": 2374}, {\"ngram\": \"this one scene\", \"from\": 2411, \"to\": 2425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Months ago, the Olympic Committeereplaced the cross on the spire of Les Invalides in Parisfor the official poster of the 2024 Olympic Games.\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2495, \"end\": 2508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.377728042992485e-37, \"text\": \"Les Invalides\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Les_Invalides\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Months ago, the Olympic Committeereplaced\", \"from\": 2427, \"to\": 2468}, {\"ngram\": \"the cross\", \"from\": 2469, \"to\": 2478}, {\"ngram\": \"the spire\", \"from\": 2482, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"Parisfor\", \"from\": 2512, \"to\": 2520}, {\"ngram\": \"the official poster\", \"from\": 2521, \"to\": 2540}, {\"ngram\": \"the 2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2566}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony in Paris also includeda scene of a threesome, adecapitated Marie Antoinette, and ratherexplicit symbols of the occult.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2592, \"end\": 2597, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999977263, \"rank\": 2.433423949384901e-12, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2648, \"end\": 2664, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.1385608154844406e-34, \"text\": \"Marie Antoinette\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie_Antoinette\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2588}, {\"ngram\": \"scene\", \"from\": 2613, \"to\": 2618}, {\"ngram\": \"ratherexplicit symbols\", \"from\": 2670, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"the occult\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2706}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The whole thing was Luciferian.\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2739, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The whole thing\", \"from\": 2708, \"to\": 2723}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Why did the organizers do this?\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the organizers\", \"from\": 2749, \"to\": 2763}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Put bluntly, they did it because they hate Jesus Christ and Christianity, which they consider their most dangerous enemy.\", \"from\": 2773, \"to\": 2894, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2816, \"end\": 2828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.170662846425606e-14, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}, {\"begin\": 2833, \"end\": 2845, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their most dangerous enemy\", \"from\": 2867, \"to\": 2893}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They are quite open about this now.\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2930, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The opening ceremony was a message, unmistakable and clear, from the European post-modern elite, that Christians are not welcome in the post-Christian, neopagan society they are creating.\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 3118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3033, \"end\": 3043, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3067, \"end\": 3081, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postchristianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"post-Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postchristianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postchristianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3083, \"end\": 3091, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0667583386567748e-50, \"text\": \"neopagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The opening ceremony\", \"from\": 2931, \"to\": 2951}, {\"ngram\": \"a message\", \"from\": 2956, \"to\": 2965}, {\"ngram\": \"the European post-modern elite\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3026}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These elites are saying, in effect, that they have tolerance for every perversity imaginable but none for the Christian faith.\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3245, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3229, \"end\": 3238, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999980389917383, \"rank\": 1.961012022253466e-06, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"These elites\", \"from\": 3119, \"to\": 3131}, {\"ngram\": \"effect\", \"from\": 3147, \"to\": 3153}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 3170, \"to\": 3179}, {\"ngram\": \"every perversity\", \"from\": 3184, \"to\": 3200}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For a long time we called this elite \\\"liberal,\\\" but they are not really liberal because liberalism requires a degree of tolerance, even for beliefs and customs liberals find repugnant.\", \"from\": 3247, \"to\": 3431, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long time\", \"from\": 3251, \"to\": 3262}, {\"ngram\": \"liberalism\", \"from\": 3335, \"to\": 3345}, {\"ngram\": \"a degree\", \"from\": 3355, \"to\": 3363}, {\"ngram\": \"tolerance\", \"from\": 3367, \"to\": 3376}, {\"ngram\": \"beliefs and customs liberals\", \"from\": 3387, \"to\": 3415}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Better to call them what they are, which is pagan or neopagan.\", \"from\": 3432, \"to\": 3494, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3476, \"end\": 3481, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4122765868512955e-12, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}, {\"begin\": 3485, \"end\": 3493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0667583386567748e-50, \"text\": \"neopagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Pagans, both ancient and modern, have no tolerance for Christianity.\", \"from\": 3495, \"to\": 3563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3495, \"end\": 3501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.9999999999763531, \"rank\": 2.3431268692207014e-11, \"text\": \"Pagans\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}, {\"begin\": 3550, \"end\": 3562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no tolerance\", \"from\": 3533, \"to\": 3545}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the greatest threat to them because it isreal, and its reality exposes the falsity of their paganism, which can only ever be a perverse imitation of the true Christian faith.\", \"from\": 3564, \"to\": 3744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3728, \"end\": 3737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999980389917383, \"rank\": 1.961012022253466e-06, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the greatest threat\", \"from\": 3570, \"to\": 3589}, {\"ngram\": \"its reality\", \"from\": 3621, \"to\": 3632}, {\"ngram\": \"the falsity\", \"from\": 3641, \"to\": 3652}, {\"ngram\": \"their paganism\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3670}, {\"ngram\": \"a perverse imitation\", \"from\": 3695, \"to\": 3715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gavin Ashenden, the former chaplain to Queen Elizabeth II, who resigned in 2017 and shortly thereafter converted to Catholicism, said Christians must raise their voices against these elites and in defense of their faith.\", \"from\": 3746, \"to\": 3966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3746, \"end\": 3760, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gavin_Ashenden\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gavin Ashenden\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gavin_Ashenden\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gavin_Ashenden\"}, {\"begin\": 3880, \"end\": 3890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the former chaplain\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3781}, {\"ngram\": \"Queen Elizabeth II\", \"from\": 3785, \"to\": 3803}, {\"ngram\": \"Catholicism\", \"from\": 3862, \"to\": 3873}, {\"ngram\": \"their voices\", \"from\": 3902, \"to\": 3914}, {\"ngram\": \"these elites\", \"from\": 3923, \"to\": 3935}, {\"ngram\": \"defense\", \"from\": 3943, \"to\": 3950}, {\"ngram\": \"their faith\", \"from\": 3954, \"to\": 3965}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We raise our voices in defense of the givenness of sexuality.\", \"from\": 3968, \"to\": 4030, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our voices\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3988}, {\"ngram\": \"defense\", \"from\": 3992, \"to\": 3999}, {\"ngram\": \"the givenness\", \"from\": 4003, \"to\": 4016}, {\"ngram\": \"sexuality\", \"from\": 4020, \"to\": 4029}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We raise our voices against perversion of human sexuality,\\\" he saidin a YouTube video over the weekend.\", \"from\": 4031, \"to\": 4134, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4103, \"end\": 4110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"score\": 0.9999999944270712, \"rank\": 5.573107610323161e-09, \"text\": \"YouTube\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/YouTube\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our voices\", \"from\": 4040, \"to\": 4050}, {\"ngram\": \"perversion\", \"from\": 4059, \"to\": 4069}, {\"ngram\": \"human sexuality\", \"from\": 4073, \"to\": 4088}, {\"ngram\": \"the weekend\", \"from\": 4122, \"to\": 4133}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For the transgender movement is above all things a specific repudiation of the givenness of human sexuality.\\\"\", \"from\": 4135, \"to\": 4245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the transgender movement\", \"from\": 4140, \"to\": 4164}, {\"ngram\": \"all things\", \"from\": 4174, \"to\": 4184}, {\"ngram\": \"a specific repudiation\", \"from\": 4185, \"to\": 4207}, {\"ngram\": \"the givenness\", \"from\": 4211, \"to\": 4224}, {\"ngram\": \"human sexuality\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4243}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He called it \\\"gender dysphoria laced with a particular kind of cyanide at the center of it: the sexualization of children by men pretending to be women.\\\"\", \"from\": 4246, \"to\": 4399, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"gender dysphoria\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4276}, {\"ngram\": \"a particular kind\", \"from\": 4288, \"to\": 4305}, {\"ngram\": \"cyanide\", \"from\": 4309, \"to\": 4316}, {\"ngram\": \"the center\", \"from\": 4320, \"to\": 4330}, {\"ngram\": \"children\", \"from\": 4359, \"to\": 4367}, {\"ngram\": \"men\", \"from\": 4371, \"to\": 4374}, {\"ngram\": \"women\", \"from\": 4392, \"to\": 4397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ashenden is right.\", \"from\": 4401, \"to\": 4419, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4401, \"end\": 4409, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashenden_(TV_series)\", \"score\": 0.9798428528080475, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashenden\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashenden_(TV_series)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashenden_(TV_series)\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The European elite who control society, who are responsible for producing public semiotics and symbols, are deeply offended by Jesus Christ and His church.\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4575, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4547, \"end\": 4559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.170662846425606e-14, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The European elite\", \"from\": 4420, \"to\": 4438}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 4451, \"to\": 4458}, {\"ngram\": \"public semiotics\", \"from\": 4494, \"to\": 4510}, {\"ngram\": \"symbols\", \"from\": 4515, \"to\": 4522}, {\"ngram\": \"His church\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4574}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They preside over a post-Christian Europe.\", \"from\": 4576, \"to\": 4618, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4596, \"end\": 4610, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postchristianity\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"post-Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postchristianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Postchristianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic France was once called the \\\"eldest daughter of the Church,\\\" but is now rapidly de-Christianizing along with the rest of the West.\", \"from\": 4619, \"to\": 4757, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4619, \"end\": 4627, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.684226164920596e-15, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 4628, \"end\": 4634, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"score\": 0.9969850852314259, \"rank\": 0.0030126735817734792, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the \\\"eldest daughter\", \"from\": 4651, \"to\": 4671}, {\"ngram\": \"the Church\", \"from\": 4675, \"to\": 4685}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 4736, \"to\": 4744}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 4748, \"to\": 4756}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The elites now feel they have enough power and dominance to come out openly against Christianity, which is what the opening ceremony of the Olympics was all about.\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4842, \"end\": 4854, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The elites\", \"from\": 4758, \"to\": 4768}, {\"ngram\": \"enough power\", \"from\": 4788, \"to\": 4800}, {\"ngram\": \"dominance\", \"from\": 4805, \"to\": 4814}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 4870, \"to\": 4890}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 4894, \"to\": 4906}]}, {\"sentence\": \"That means Christians will have to fight back.\", \"from\": 4923, \"to\": 4969, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4934, \"end\": 4944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Commenting on this over the weekend, Elon Muskposted on Xthat, \\\"Unless there is more bravery to stand up for what is fair and right, Christianity will perish.\\\"\", \"from\": 4970, \"to\": 5129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5103, \"end\": 5115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the weekend\", \"from\": 4994, \"to\": 5005}, {\"ngram\": \"Xthat\", \"from\": 5026, \"to\": 5031}, {\"ngram\": \"more bravery\", \"from\": 5050, \"to\": 5062}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As Christians, we know that Christianity will never perish from the earth.\", \"from\": 5130, \"to\": 5204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5133, \"end\": 5143, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 5158, \"end\": 5170, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the earth\", \"from\": 5194, \"to\": 5203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But insofar as Musk meant that Christendom or Western civilization will perish unless Christians are brave enough to stand up for the faith that created the West, he has a point.\", \"from\": 5205, \"to\": 5383, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5236, \"end\": 5247, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9694113247744565, \"rank\": 0.031553866190723805, \"text\": \"Christendom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 5291, \"end\": 5301, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Musk\", \"from\": 5220, \"to\": 5224}, {\"ngram\": \"the faith\", \"from\": 5335, \"to\": 5344}, {\"ngram\": \"the West\", \"from\": 5358, \"to\": 5366}, {\"ngram\": \"a point\", \"from\": 5375, \"to\": 5382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christians of an earlier era knew how to deal with pagans who hated Jesus Christ.\", \"from\": 5385, \"to\": 5466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5385, \"end\": 5395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 5453, \"end\": 5465, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.170662846425606e-14, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an earlier era\", \"from\": 5399, \"to\": 5413}, {\"ngram\": \"pagans\", \"from\": 5436, \"to\": 5442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"First, they bore witness to Christ's conquest over death by becoming willing martyrs for the faith.\", \"from\": 5467, \"to\": 5566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5495, \"end\": 5501, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3810120664257554e-14, \"text\": \"Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"witness\", \"from\": 5484, \"to\": 5491}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 5518, \"to\": 5523}, {\"ngram\": \"willing martyrs\", \"from\": 5536, \"to\": 5551}, {\"ngram\": \"the faith\", \"from\": 5556, \"to\": 5565}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Later, they defended the faith against Islam and pagan armies alike.\", \"from\": 5567, \"to\": 5635, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5616, \"end\": 5621, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.9999999999986358, \"rank\": 1.4122765868512955e-12, \"text\": \"pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the faith\", \"from\": 5588, \"to\": 5597}, {\"ngram\": \"Islam\", \"from\": 5606, \"to\": 5611}, {\"ngram\": \"armies\", \"from\": 5622, \"to\": 5628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They were willing to stand firm for Christ, whether it meant dying as a martyr or as a soldier on the battlefield.\", \"from\": 5636, \"to\": 5750, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Christ\", \"from\": 5672, \"to\": 5678}, {\"ngram\": \"a martyr\", \"from\": 5706, \"to\": 5714}, {\"ngram\": \"a soldier\", \"from\": 5721, \"to\": 5730}, {\"ngram\": \"the battlefield\", \"from\": 5734, \"to\": 5749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In our time, Christians will have to rediscover that spirit and that courage.\", \"from\": 5752, \"to\": 5829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5765, \"end\": 5775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our time\", \"from\": 5755, \"to\": 5763}, {\"ngram\": \"that spirit\", \"from\": 5800, \"to\": 5811}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The days of being left alone by powerful elites who control society are over.\", \"from\": 5830, \"to\": 5907, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The days\", \"from\": 5830, \"to\": 5838}, {\"ngram\": \"powerful elites\", \"from\": 5862, \"to\": 5877}, {\"ngram\": \"society\", \"from\": 5890, \"to\": 5897}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Europe does not just mock Christianity, it is also in the process of criminalizing the faith with laws and regulations designed to punish the faithful, like prohibiting silent prayer within a certain distance of abortion clinics, to give but one example among many.\", \"from\": 5908, \"to\": 6173, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5934, \"end\": 5946, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Europe\", \"from\": 5908, \"to\": 5914}, {\"ngram\": \"the process\", \"from\": 5962, \"to\": 5973}, {\"ngram\": \"the faith\", \"from\": 5991, \"to\": 6000}, {\"ngram\": \"laws\", \"from\": 6006, \"to\": 6010}, {\"ngram\": \"regulations\", \"from\": 6015, \"to\": 6026}, {\"ngram\": \"silent prayer\", \"from\": 6077, \"to\": 6090}, {\"ngram\": \"a certain distance\", \"from\": 6098, \"to\": 6116}, {\"ngram\": \"abortion clinics\", \"from\": 6120, \"to\": 6136}, {\"ngram\": \"one example\", \"from\": 6150, \"to\": 6161}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The same sort of thing will eventually happen in America.\", \"from\": 6175, \"to\": 6232, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The same sort\", \"from\": 6175, \"to\": 6188}, {\"ngram\": \"thing\", \"from\": 6192, \"to\": 6197}, {\"ngram\": \"America\", \"from\": 6224, \"to\": 6231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Vice President Kamala Harris, the Democratic Party's putative nominee for president, went on record years ago as a U.S. senator to say any Catholic man who is a member of the Knights of Columbus is unfit for public office.\", \"from\": 6233, \"to\": 6455, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6248, \"end\": 6254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamala_Harris\", \"score