://dbpedia.org/resource/Oval_Office\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the power\", \"from\": 6504, \"to\": 6513}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christians need to be prepared to speak out against the mockery of their faith by neopagan elites.\", \"from\": 6535, \"to\": 6633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6535, \"end\": 6545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 6617, \"end\": 6625, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0667583386567748e-50, \"text\": \"neopagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Modern_Paganism\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the mockery\", \"from\": 6587, \"to\": 6598}, {\"ngram\": \"their faith\", \"from\": 6602, \"to\": 6613}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They also need to be prepared to fight, suffer, and perhaps die for their faith.\", \"from\": 6634, \"to\": 6714, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their faith\", \"from\": 6702, \"to\": 6713}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In that, we Christians can take heart.\", \"from\": 6716, \"to\": 6754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6728, \"end\": 6738, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999715364291721, \"rank\": 2.8397653987295124e-05, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"heart\", \"from\": 6748, \"to\": 6753}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have a long history of fighting and dying for our faith-and what's more, a faith that can overcome death.\", \"from\": 6755, \"to\": 6863, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a long history\", \"from\": 6763, \"to\": 6777}, {\"ngram\": \"our faith\", \"from\": 6804, \"to\": 6813}, {\"ngram\": \"death\", \"from\": 6857, \"to\": 6862}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As G.K. Chesterton wrote, \\\"Christendom has had a series of revolutions and in each one of them Christianity has died.\", \"from\": 6864, \"to\": 6981, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6872, \"end\": 6882, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G._K._Chesterton\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.346866635036763e-22, \"text\": \"Chesterton\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q36180\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G._K._Chesterton\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/G._K._Chesterton\"}, {\"begin\": 6891, \"end\": 6902, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9694113247744565, \"rank\": 0.031553866190723805, \"text\": \"Christendom\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 6959, \"end\": 6971, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a series\", \"from\": 6911, \"to\": 6919}, {\"ngram\": \"revolutions\", \"from\": 6923, \"to\": 6934}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Christianity has died many times and risen again; for it had a God who knew the way out of the grave.\\\"\", \"from\": 6982, \"to\": 7084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6982, \"end\": 6994, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.999999487050122, \"rank\": 5.056153704150656e-07, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a God\", \"from\": 7043, \"to\